When Cursor auto-generates a Git commit message for this repository (Source Control sparkle button), you MUST follow these rules strictly.

<format>
<type>(<scope>): <description>

[optional body explaining WHY, not how]
</format>

<rules>
- **Spec**: Conventional Commits standard.
- **Output Language**: The `<description>` and `[body]` MUST be written EXCLUSIVELY in Korean.
- **Termination Rule**: `<description>` MUST end with a noun-phrase termination ONLY (e.g., ~구현, ~수정, ~추가, ~제거, ~개선).
- **Prohibited Verbs**: NEVER use past tense or sentence-ending verbs (❌ ~했음, ~함, ~했습니다, ~완료).
</rules>

<constraints>
- **Length**: Subject line (first line) MUST be less than or equal to 50 characters.
- **Spacing**: Exactly one space after the colon (e.g., `feat: 메시지`).
- **No Period**: NEVER end the subject line with a period (`.`).
- **Monorepo Scope**: Every commit MUST specify a precise package/domain as the `<scope>` (e.g., `backend`, `frontend`, `auth`, `root`, `lecture`, `courses`). Broad or vague scopes are strictly prohibited.
</constraints>

<types>
- `feat`: New feature
- `fix`: Bug fix
- `docs`: Documentation changes
- `style`: Code formatting/linting (no logic change)
- `refactor`: Code restructuring (no fix/feature)
- `test`: Adding/modifying tests
- `ci`: CI/CD workflows, build scripts (GitHub Actions)
- `chore`: Build tasks, pnpm, tool configs (.eslintrc, .cursorrules)
- `perf`: Performance improvement
</types>

<examples>
feat(backend): JWT 기반 액세스 토큰 발급 기능 구현
fix(frontend): 모바일 뷰 결제 버튼 미정렬 오류 수정
docs(root): README 문서에 테스트 전략 가이드라인 추가
refactor(auth): 중복 회원 검증 로직을 커스텀 가드로 분리
test(courses): 강의 생성 통합 테스트 코드 추가
chore(root): pnpm 워크스페이스 패키지 의존성 최적화
</examples>
